	<title>The rank of a system of linear equations</title>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the rank of the system of linear equations</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\begin{array}{rcrcrcr}
x & + & 3y & & & = & 4 \\
  &   &    & & z & = & -1
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>The coefficient matrix of this system of linear equations is</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\begin{array}{rrr|r}
{\color{red} 1} & 3 & 0 & 4 \\
0 & 0 & {\color{red} 1} & -1
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>The non-augmented coefficient matrix has two leading 1&rsquo;s. Therefore the rank of this system of linear equations is <latex>2</latex>.</para>
		</answer>
	</showme>
	
	
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Suppose a system of linear equations has a coefficient matrix which row reduces to </para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\begin{array}{rrrrrr|r}
1 & 3 & 0 & 0 & 7 & 0 & 1 \\
0 & 0 & 1 & 0 & 5 & 0 & -1 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & 1 & 1 & 0 & 4 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 1 & 5
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>Find the rank of the system.</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>Indeed, the given matrix is already in RREF. Let us identify its leading 1&rsquo;s:</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\begin{array}{rrrrrr|r}
{\color{red} 1} & 3 & 0 & 0 & 7 & 0 & 1 \\
0 & 0 & {\color{red} 1} & 0 & 5 & 0 & -1 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & {\color{red} 1} & 1 & 0 & 4 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & {\color{red} 1} & 5
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>So the non-augmented part of the row reduced coefficient matrix contains 4 leading 1&rsquo;s. Therefore the rank of this system of linear equations is 4.</para>
		</answer>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>